snippet.textDisplay: One thing I noticed was this video did a really great job showing a variety of switches. I’ve heard a lot about people invalidating people with DID because their switches don’t seem ‘right’ or are different from others, but this video showed how diverse they can be, with the redwoods system having quick, frequent switches, the dissociaDID system having a few long switches and the other system having none at all, while still all being completely valid. Great video

Personally, I enjoyed watching Split and it's one of my favourite movies ever. But to the people who think it's real are just imbeciles who are too gullible. It's just a movie. Not actual people with actual DID are gonna turn into The Beast or something. It's both offensive to them, and the creator of the movie because one, the creator had ambition and creativity of making it into an interesting trilogy and talking bad about it makes it even worse. Sure, you can have your own opinions and whatever, but don't be so rude you start a riot on the internet. The people who put work into that movie gave in millions of dollars.

Second, it's offensive to the people who do have DID because other people are thinking they're bad because those people are so stupid to believe that Split will happen in real life. It's a goddamn movie.

I think it would be nice to have some research links in the description for those like me or even more skeptical ones. Of course if we are talking about something like this, not every time (it's much easier for me to understand a teacher or a stripper than someone with DID). I'm not saying these people were fake, I'm just saying it's good to have scientific proofs attached to serious topics like these. We have to trust people but internet is internet, you know,  it makes you very skeptical sometimes
